\f0\b\fs40 \cf0 COVID-19 Mortality and Environmental Factors Analysis\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf0 About the Project\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf0 This repository contains the analysis code and datasets for an epidemiological study examining the relationship between COVID-19 mortality rates and environmental factors (UV index, ambient temperature, and sunlight duration). The core analysis utilizes a 
\f0\b Distributed Lag Model (DLM)
\f1\b0  focusing on 7 to 21-day lag windows, controlling for socioeconomic and other environmental confounding variables.\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 Repository Structure\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf0 The repository is organized into three main components: data collection (Python), statistical analysis (MATLAB), and the raw datasets.\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 1. Main Analysis Scripts (MATLAB)\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0
\f2\b0\fs18 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 MAIN_ANALYSIS.mlx
\f1\b0 : The backbone of the study.\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs18 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 Standardizes environmental variables (UV, Temperature, Sunlight) using Z-scores.\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 Fits a Fixed Effects model with a Poisson distribution, accounting for 7-21 day lags.\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 Visualizes model fit, standardized effect sizes (via Forest Plots), and regional time-series reconstructions.\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 Exports the final metrics and coefficients to Model_Standardized_7to21Lags.xlsx.\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 REGION-SPECIFIC_ANALYSIS.mlx
\f1\b0 : Executes isolated, region-specific analyses for all countries and states included in the dataset to evaluate localized effects.\
\ls1\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 diagnostics.mlx
\f1\b0 : Runs essential statistical assumption tests and model diagnostics for the Generalized Linear Models (GLM) after the main analysis is complete.\
\ls1\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 summary.mlx
\f1\b0 : Generates descriptive statistics (Mean, Variance, Min, Max) for all raw inputs used in the study. Exports the results directly to a supplementary Excel file.\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

