\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 How to Run\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls6\ilvl0
\f1\b0\fs26 \cf0 {\listtext	0.	}
\f0\b Prerequisites:
\f1\b0  You must have 
\f0\b MATLAB
\f1\b0  installed, including the Statistics and Machine Learning Toolbox.\
{\listtext	0.	}
\f0\b Working Directory:
\f1\b0  Ensure all .mlx scripts and .xlsx/.csv data files are placed in the same working directory.\
{\listtext	0.	}
\f0\b Descriptive Statistics:
\f1\b0  Run summary.mlx first to generate an overview of the input data.\
{\listtext	0.	}
\f0\b Main Analysis:
\f1\b0  Run MAIN_ANALYSIS.mlx from start to finish to fit the primary models, generate the core figures (Fig 1-5), and automate the Excel exports.\
{\listtext	0.	}
\f0\b Diagnostics:
\f1\b0  Run diagnostics.mlx to validate the assumptions of the main models.\
{\listtext	0.	}
\f0\b Regional Breakdown:
\f1\b0  Finally, execute REGION-SPECIFIC_ANALYSIS.mlx to isolate and examine the effects within specific countries or states.\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

